%U A397119 5276754306100,29942798197617,169909619789731,964147586639560,5471029854962274,31045212984269965,176165234363883577,999644927710662492
%N A397119 Size of clusters of star triples of Family E in the Spectre aperiodic monotile tiling.
%C A397119 The chiral aperiodic Spectre monotile tiling (discovered in 2023) forms hierarchical, fractal macro-structures called clusters of star triples (three Spectre tiles head-on) of five different families, megastars of two types, and palindromes of megastars. This sequence represents the total number of star triples in successive generations of Family E clusters. The fractal growth is governed by the limiting constant 5.674473356937... = 1 + 2*sqrt(6) * cos((1/3) * arccos(sqrt(6)/4)), which is the largest root of the cubic equation x^3 - 3*x^2 - 15*x - 1 = 0.
%H A397119 Boris K. Horvat, <a href="/A397119/b397119.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..100</a>
%H A397119 Boris K. Horvat, <a href="https://zenodo.org/records/18421797">Anatomy of the Spectre Tiling</a>, Zenodo, 2026.
%H A397119 David Smith, J. S. Myers, C. S. Kaplan, and C. Goodman-Strauss, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.17743">A chiral aperiodic monotile</a>, arXiv:2305.17743 [math.CO], 2023-2024.
%H A397119 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (4,12,-14,-1).
%F A397119 a(n) = 3*a(n-1) + 15*a(n-2) + a(n-3) + 12 (for n>3, where a(1)=4, a(2)=25, a(3)=147).
%F A397119 a(n) = 4*a(n-1) + 12*a(n-2) - 14*a(n-3) - a(n-4) (for n>3, where a(0)=0, a(1)=4, a(2)=25, a(3)=147).
%F A397119 a(n) = a(n-1) + A397120(n) + A397121(n) + A397122(n) (for n>0, with a(0)=0).
%F A397119 a(n) = A397118(n) + A397122(n) (for n>0).
%F A397119 a(n) = c_1*r_1^n + c_2*r_2^n + c_3*r_3^n - 2/3, where r_1, r_2, r_3 are the roots of x^3 - 3*x^2 - 15*x - 1 = 0.
%F A397119 G.f.: x*(4 + 9*x - x^2)/((1 - x)*(1 - 3*x - 15*x^2 - x^3)). - _Stefano Spezia_, Jun 27 2026
%e A397119 For n = 2, the cluster of Family E has a(2) = 25 star triples. It is formed by the previous generation's cluster a(1) = 4 and is inflated/extended by one Type A megastar of size MA(2) = 4, by one Type C megastar of size MC(2) = 7, and by a palindrome of all Type A megastars up to generation 2, PA(2) = 10, giving 4 + 4 + 7 + 10 = 25 star triples.
%e A397119 For n = 3, the cluster of Family E has a(3) = 147 star triples. It is formed by the previous generation's cluster a(2) = 25 and is inflated/extended by one Type A megastar of size MA(3) = 25, by one Type C megastar of size MC(3) = 37, and by a palindrome of all Type A megastars up to generation 3, PA(3) = 60, giving 25 + 25 + 37 + 60 = 147 star triples.
%t A397119 LinearRecurrence[{4, 12, -14, -1}, {4, 25, 147, 832}, 24] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 27 2026 *)
%Y A397119 Cf. A397115 (Family A), A397116 (Family C), A397117 (Family B), A397118 (Family D), A397120 (Megastar A), A397121 (Megastar C), A397122 (Palindrome A), A397123 (Sequence A).
